<item>
            <title>[TIKA-4201] Add hard limit to stream reading in IWorksParser#detectType</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-4201</link>
                <project id="12310631" key="TIKA">Tika</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TIKA-4199&quot; title=&quot;commons-compress 1.26.0 breaks Apache Tika 2.9.1&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;TIKA-4199&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;TIKA-4199&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; showed us that we had been relying on hope that the detector would only read a limited number of bytes when detecting in IWorksParser#detectType. We should cache the first 1096 bytes, do the detection, and then reset the wrapped archive stream. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should not rely on hope.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
